2 CONT James Taylor of Magerville in the County of Sunbury and Province of New Brunswick Esquire being duly sworn desposeth and saith That he has for several months past received very injurious treatment from Abijah Palmer Junior of the same place--That t
2 CONC he said Abijah Palmer has in several instances attempted (as the Desponent has good reason to believe) to injure the Family and Property of the Desponent--That the said Abijah Palmer has been (in the opinion and belief of the desponent) instigato
2 CONC r thereto not only by the wicked and malicious suggestions of his own mind but by the persuasion of his the said Abijah's father.  And the Desponent further saith that his two Daughters Mary Robinson Bridges (wife of Samuel Bridges Junior, and Eliz
2 CONC abeth Archibald Taylor, Spinister) have very lately been arrested and held in Custody of the Sheriff of Sunbury upon the Complaint (as the desponent in well informed) of the said Abijah Palmer upon a charge against them for murder--That upon the ex
2 CONC amination of the magistrates into the said complaint his said Daughters were liberated by the direction (as the desponent was informed) of the Chief Justice of the Province--And the desponent further saith that it haas been given in 
