2 TITL Bragg Family Origins
1 _OID 2460dccc-bd4e-4cd6-88de-d130cea967ca
1 DATE 21 Sep 2016
1 PLAC Crewkerne, Somerset, England
1 _META <metadataxml><content><line>&lt;p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-: 10px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #36322d; font-family: 'source sans pro', 'helvetica neue', arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="box-sizing: inh
2 CONC erit; color: #262626;"&gt;The Bragg surname is of Norman origin and is interwoven withBritish history. The first record of the Bragg name was found 1066 inCambridgeshire records where lands where granted by Duke William of Normandy.The original for
2 CONC m was Braggi a Norman word meaning hero and eventually became&amp;ldquo;a man of great accomplishment&amp;rdquo;. Later the name morphed into a common term fora boaster or braggart.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p style
2 CONC ="box-sizing: inherit; margin-: 10px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #36322d; font-family: 'source sans pro', 'helvetica neue', arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p style="box-sizing: inherit; mar
2 CONC gin-: 10px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #36322d; font-family: 'source sans pro', 'helvetica neue', arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="box-sizing: inherit; color: #262626;"&gt;As the centuries passed the family nam
2 CONC e was spelled eitherBragge or Bragg, and interchangeably between generations. The Bragg familysettled mainly in the West Country in the counties of Devon, Somerset andDover. The earliest descendants of the Bragg line that migrated to NorthAmerica i
2 CONC n the mid-1600&amp;rsquo;s came from Somersetshire and Devonshire.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-: 10px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #36322d; font-family: 'source sans pro', 'helv
2 CONC etica neue', arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-: 10px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #36322d; font-family: 'source sans pro', 'helvetica neue', arial, sans-s
2 CONC erif; font-size: 16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="box-sizing: inherit; color: #262626;"&gt;The reason for the Bragg migration to North America in the1600&amp;rsquo;s is tied to the political and religious upheavals of the English CivilWar. The West Countr
2 CONC y people where primarily royalists and protestant.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-: 10px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #36322d; font-family: 'source sans pro', 'helvetica neue', ari
2 CONC al, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-: 10px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #36322d; font-family: 'source sans pro', 'helvetica neue', arial, sans-serif; font-size
2 CONC : 16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="box-sizing: inherit; color: #262626;"&gt;The Origins of the English Civil War&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-: 10px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #36322d
2 CONC ; font-family: 'source sans pro', 'helvetica neue', arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-: 10px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #36322d; font-family: 'source san
2 CONC s pro', 'helvetica neue', arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="box-sizing: inherit; color: #262626;"&gt;King James VI of Scotland became King of England in 1603 and thusJames the first. This was the beginning of the Stuart line
2 CONC . James wasresponsible for a new translation of the Bible, the King James Version,published in 1611.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-: 10px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #36322d; fon
2 CONC t-family: 'source sans pro', 'helvetica neue', arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-: 10px; margin-bottom: 0px; padding: 0px; color: #36322d; font-family: 'source sans pro
2 CONC ', 'helvetica neue', arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px;"&gt;&lt;span style="box-sizing: inherit; color: #262626;"&gt;King James came into conflict with Parliament over the cost offoreign wars, which were supported by rents on royal lands. The situ
2 CONC ation was furthercomplicated by disagreements over religion. Many Members of Parliament (MP&amp;rsquo;s)were Puritans who wished to purify the Church of England of its remainingCatholics. Although James was a Protestant he disagreed with this polic
2 CONC y. Jamesalso believed in the divine right of Kings. In other words he believed God hadchosen him to rule and thus the government was subservient to him.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p style="box-sizing: inherit; margin-: 10px; m
