1 _META <metadataxml><content><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color: #333333; font-family: 'helvetica neue', arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; line-height: 16px;"&gt;Elishu Gunnison, Esq., Kittery, Sheepscot, Pemaquid, Falmouth. &amp;nbsp;He was the sixt
2 CONC h child and youngest son of Hugh Gunnison, and was born in Boston 12 Feb. 1650, and died after March 29, 1729.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color: #333333; font-family: 'helvetica neue', arial, sans-serif; font-size
2 CONC : small; line-height: 16px;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color: #333333; font-family: 'helvetica neue', arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; line-height: 16px;"&gt;A Shiprwight by occupation, he early w
2 CONC orked for Mr. Hendersonand and settled on his father's "300 acres, at Spruce Creek where he built a mill and had a yard; in 1695, only son and husband, he was tryihnjg to dispossess Richa5rd Endie as a treapsser on this grant."&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&g
2 CONC t;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color: #333333; font-family: 'helvetica neue', arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; line-height: 16px;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color: #333333; font-family: '
2 CONC helvetica neue', arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; line-height: 16px;"&gt;He became a man of considerable influence among townsmen. &amp;nbsp;Portsmouth minister's ratebabated &amp;nbsp;March 1679-80, &amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color
2 CONC : #333333; font-family: 'helvetica neue', arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; line-height: 16px;"&gt;In 1680 he joined with other inhabitants of York, kittery, and Wells in an address to Charles Ii, praying to be relieved of the Puritan governmen
2 CONC t of Boston, and in the same year he was acting as Magistrate.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color: #333333; font-family: 'helvetica neue', arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; line-height: 16px;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line>
2 CONC <line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color: #333333; font-family: 'helvetica neue', arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; line-height: 16px;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color: #333333; font-family: 'helvetic
2 CONC a neue', arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; line-height: 16px;"&gt;Preparing to move East, he mortaged his Kittery house to in June 1683, discharged before April 1697.&amp;nbsp; Sheepscot April 1684-1685; grant Buckland's Neck, at jamestown 1686.
2 CONC &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Justice of the Peace for Cornwall Co. 1684-6.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; He signed a Pemaquid petition as resident in May 1689, but had just arrived from Casco; at Falmouth August following and 13 November member of Council of War the
2 CONC re when ordered that a garrison be erected about his house at Falmouth to be the main court of Guard. &amp;nbsp;Representatve from Kittery 1693, and was chosen as a Selectman 1693-97, 1710,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color: #333333; font
2 CONC -family: 'helvetica neue', arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; line-height: 16px;"&gt;On May 9, 1693, he was appointed with others to give instructions to the deputy of the representatives to the General Court at Boston.&amp;nbsp; From 1699-1726 h
2 CONC e was moderator of the Town.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color: #333333; font-family: 'helvetica neue', arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; line-height: 16px;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="col
2 CONC or: #333333; font-family: 'helvetica neue', arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; line-height: 16px;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color: #333333; font-family: 'helvetica neue', arial, sans-serif; font-si
2 CONC ze: small; line-height: 16px;"&gt;He married 1st November 10, 1674 Martha Trickey; in 1680 his Petition about Thomas Trickey's estate put on file. &amp;nbsp;By her, he had four children&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="co
2 CONC lor: #333333; font-family: 'helvetica neue', arial, sans-serif; font-size: small; line-height: 16px;"&gt;He married 2nd&amp;nbsp; by 1690&amp;nbsp; Elizabeth (Ingersoll), widow of John Skillings. &amp;nbsp;By her, he had two children.&lt;/span&gt;&
