2 CONC ch: inherit; line-height: 26.25px;"&gt;1. Nathaniel Hammond died 1749; m. Margaret Stone who d. 1776. Children: 1. Benjamin Hammond b. June 7, 1724; is said to have commanded a company of militia at Lexington, April 19, 1775 and did other militar
2 CONC y duty; afterwards a Colonel; was a long time a leading man in the municipal affairs of Newton. In advanced life he went to Rutland and lived with his son-in-law, Jonas Read. He m. Oct 5, 1749, Sarah Brown by whom he had 9 children. His 5th child
2 CONC , Anna Hammond m. 1777, Rev. Joseph Pope of Spencer who grad. Harvard College 1770 and d. 1826. Children: 1. Joseph Hammond b. July 14, 1778; grad. Dartmouth College 1798; a lawyer, of Portland, Maine. 2. Charles Hammond b. Feb 26, 1780. 3. Willia
2 CONC m Hammond b. Dec 10, 1781; a magistrate of Spencer. 4. Anna Hammond b. Feb 16, 1786; m. Sept 1809, Rev. Roswell Shurtleff, D.D., then and afterwards a professor in Dartmouth College. Benjamin Hammond was one of the most prominent men of the localit
2 CONC y in his day, both in civil and military life. He was Selectman from 1767 to 1776, and held many of the town offices after the close of the war. His assessment was one of the largest in Newton. After the death of his wife he went to Rutland to liv
2 CONC e with his daughter, Mrs. Read.&lt;/p&gt;</line></content></metadataxml>
