2 TITL 18171205 Last Will and Testament of James Guppy 007131961_00330
1 _OID 64a4b43e-9589-4959-9c59-5198d62f57e4
1 DATE 05 Dec 1917
1 PLAC Dover, Strafford, New Hampshire, USA
1 _DSCR Last Will and Testament of James Guppy, written on December 5, 1817.
1 _META <metadataxml><transcription>Pg 151 &amp; 152
2 CONT James Guppy 
2 CONT Will
2 CONT Be it known to all people to whom these presents shall come that I James Guppy of Dover in the county of Strafford and State of New Hampshire husbandman being weak in body but of sound disposing mind &amp; memory considering the uncertainly of huma
2 CONC n life and being desirous to settle my worldly affairs while I have strength and capacity so to do---  Do make and publish this my last will and testament and therein and thereby dispose of all my worldly Estate in manner following to wit. ___ 
2 CONT Firstly I give bequeath and devise unto my beloved wife Ann Guppy all my household furniture and one half of all my buildings in Dover, also on quarter part of the produce of all my lands in said Dover and in Somersworth in said County and one quar
2 CONC ter part of all the income of all my [neat] stock of cattle sheep and hogs and of every other thing whatsoever name or nature to be delivered to her yearly and in due season each year free of expense, and also wood for a comfortable fire cut up a
2 CONC t the door, all to be provided and delivered by my Executor hereafter named, to have and to hold said one half of said buildings during her natural life.
2 CONT Secondly I give and bequeath to my son John Guppy all my homestead farm with the buildings thereon in said Dover &amp; Somersworth and all my stock of cattle sheep and hogs and every other kind of real and personal estate wherever the same may be s
2 CONC ituated or found except such as are otherwise disposed of and those bequeathed to his Mother to have and to hold the same to him and his heirs forever.----
2 CONT Thirdly I give and bequeath to my son Samuel Guppy one dollar to be paid him by my Executor whenever thereto required.
2 CONT Fourthly I give and bequeath to my son George Guppy two hundred dollars to be paid by my Executor within three years after my decease.----
2 CONT Fifthly I give and bequeath to my son James Guppy if living one dollar to be paid when called for my him or his lawful heirs by my Executor. ---
2 CONT Sixthly I give and bequeath to my daughter Ann Guppy one dollar to be paid by my Executor within three years after my decease or when the same shall be legally demanded. -----
2 CONT Seventhly I give and bequeath to my daughters Jane Clements, Prudence Hanson, and Abigail Dame fifty dollars each to be paid by my executor within three years after my decease.__
2 CONT Lastly I hereby nominate constitute and appoint my said son John Guppy to be Executor of this my last will and testament hereby revoking all others by me heretofore made.
2 CONT In testimony whereof I the said James Guppy have to this my last will and testament set my hand and seal this fifth day of December in the year of our Lord one thousand eight hundred and seventeen signed James Guppy[seal]  sealed published and decl
2 CONC ared by the above James Guppy as and for his last will and testament in presence of us who at his request in his presence &amp; in presence of each other have subscribed our names as witnesses thereunto
2 CONT Moses L. Neal
2 CONT Jonathan Locke
2 CONT Moses L. Neal Jr.</transcription></metadataxml>
