1 _DSCR --Bio of John Ball families.  Source:  Old Kittery and Her Families, by Everett Stackpole, 1903 (p282)
1 _META <metadataxml><content><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #262626;"&gt;John Ball [I] had a grant at Agamenticus in 1649 and was a juryman the same year&amp;hellip;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;spa
2 CONC n style="color: #262626; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: small; line-height: 1.3;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #
2 CONC 262626;"&gt;John Ball [II], perhaps son of the John Ball named above, bought land on the west side of Spruce Creek in 1667.&lt;span style="mso-spacerun: yes;"&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;Depositions in 1716 gave his age as about 80 and his &lt;spa
2 CONC n style="text-decoration: underline;"&gt;wife, Joanna&amp;rsquo;s&lt;/span&gt;, as about 70 (York Deeds, X. 34).&lt;span style="mso-spacerun: yes;"&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;He sent a petition to Governor Andros in about 1687, saying that he had s
2 CONC erved in the Indian wars without recompense and mentioning his &amp;ldquo;numerous family.&amp;rdquo;&lt;span style="mso-spacerun: yes;"&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;In 1702 John Ball administered the estate of his father&amp;rsquo;s brother, Richar
2 CONC d Ball, fisherman.&lt;span style="mso-spacerun: yes;"&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;He and wife Joanna, &lt;span style="text-decoration: underline;"&gt;sold their homestead&lt;/span&gt; to son-in-law, Francis Pettegrew, for maintenance the rest of the
2 CONC ir lives, &lt;span style="text-decoration: underline;"&gt;17 June 1717&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span style="mso-spacerun: yes;"&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;The following seem to have been their children:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;spa
2 CONC n style="font-size: small; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #262626;"&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;John [III], had lot laid out in 1698; &lt;span style="text-decoration: underline;"&gt;m. Anne Allen 9 Dec. 1717&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
2 CONC &lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #262626;"&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Elizabeth m. Edward Hammons 20 Oct 1700 (2) Francis Pettegrew.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>
2 CONC &lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #262626;"&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Mary m Joseph Crocket, Jr., 12 Oct 1700&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small; fon
2 CONC t-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #262626;"&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;William.&lt;span style="mso-spacerun: yes;"&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;His widow, Mary, administered his estate in 1695.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&l
2 CONC t;span style="font-size: small; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; color: #262626;"&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Joanna m. Benjamin Hutchins.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif
