1 _DSCR Osmond Dutch of Bridport, Dorset, was likely descended from 1 of the 7 "Douchemen" listed in the Dorset Muster Roll of 1530 (a time when universal surnames 1st became required); of whom 1st listed was "Willym Douche" (who'd apparently assumed/bee
2 CONC n given the descriptive surname "DUTCH." Others in group prob. took the same surname) - hence there was no prior coat of arms.
