1 _DSCR SAMUEL HARMON &amp; Family;
1 _META <metadataxml><content><line>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;SAMUEL HARMON {John), b. June 15, 1686, Wells, Me., m. &lt;br&gt;Mar. 19, 1707, Mercy Simpson, at Wells. She was b. Mar. 11, 1683, at &lt;br&gt;Ipswich, Mass., and wa
2 CONC s a dau. of George and Alice (Phillips) Simpson. &lt;br&gt;(See Simpson family). Samuel Harmon purchased several large tracts of &lt;br&gt;land at Scottaway Hill in Scarboro, Me., built a mill on the river there, &lt;br&gt;known as Harmon's Mill, a
2 CONC nd settled at the place in 1728. He became a &lt;br&gt;comfortable land owner, a representative man of the section and resided there &lt;br&gt;until his death, which occured about 1777. In 1728 he was appointed one &lt;br&gt;of a committee to see
2 CONC k a minister for the town, which had no minister up to &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Children: [this time. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Mercy, b. 1710, m. Nov. 29, 1729, Moses Burnham, in Scarboro. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Samuel, Jr., b. 1711, m. Nov. 24, 1733, Catherin
2 CONC e Goodale. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Sarah, b. 1713, m. Oct. 17, 1732, John Coolbroth, in Scarboro. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;John, b. 1716, m. 1st., Dec. 2, 1742, Mary Hasty, m. 2nd., May 30, &lt;br&gt;1754, Abigail Foss, m. 3d., Abigail Hoyt. &lt;br&gt;&lt;b
2 CONC r&gt;William, b. 1719, m. Jan. 19, 1740, Esther Libby. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;James, b. 1721, m. Oct. 27, 1743, Elizabeth Small. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;12 THE HARMON GENEALOGY. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Ester, b. 1723, m. Mar. 29, 1753, Jon
2 CONC athan Milliken. &lt;br&gt;George, b. July 18, 1730, m. Nov. 26, 1760, Mary Foss. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;(From a record of A. K. P. Meserve, 1890.) &lt;br&gt;The Simpson Family. &lt;br&gt;George Simpson, of Ipswich, Mass., in 1668, m. July 22, 1676, Al
2 CONC ice &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Phillips, and had the following children : &lt;br&gt;George, b. Aug. 17, 1677, d. aged 1 yr. &lt;br&gt;Richard, b. Mar. 10, 1679, prob. m. July 14. 1702, Mary Lufkin. He &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;lived in Wells, Me. &lt;br&gt;Eliz
2 CONC abeth, b. Jan. 11, 1681. &lt;br&gt;--Mercy, b. Mar. 11, 1683, m. Mar. 17, 1707, Samuel Harmon. &lt;br&gt;Alice, b. Feb. 18, 1685. Sarah, b. June 14, 1691. &lt;br&gt;John, b. Aug. 27, 1694. Mary, b. Mar. 4, 1696.&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;b
