1 _OID aa376d99-5fa1-4ac4-b26f-89b80100244e
1 DATE 1641-1656
1 PLAC Portsmouth, NH
1 _DSCR Renald (or Reginald) Fernald, who came to Portsmouth, NH in 1631 and his family as reported in &quot;Old Kittery and Her Families&quot; by Everett Stackpole, and the generations that followed.
1 _META <metadataxml><content><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: large;"&gt;The following is found in &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Old Kittery and Her Families&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;by Everett Schermerhorn Stackpole; Harvard College Library, 1931.&amp
2 CONC ;nbsp; (This source can be downloaded for free from Google eBooks.)&lt;br&gt;Page 375:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: large;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;FERNALD&lt;br&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;(Note at bottom of th
2 CONC e page states: Prepared by Prof. H.T. Fernald of Amherst, Mass.&amp;nbsp; Mr. Harry W. Fernald of Roxbury, Mass., has also been consulted.)&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: large;"&gt;Renald (also cal
2 CONC led Reginald) Fernald came to Portsmouth in 1631 as the surgeon of Capt. John Mason's Company.&amp;nbsp; It is a tradition that he was a surgeon in the English Navy, resigning his post to come to America.&amp;nbsp; He was Clerk of Court, Recorder o
2 CONC f Deeds, Commissioner, and Surveyor, and was Town Clerk at the time of his death.&amp;nbsp; He lived on "Doctor's," now Peirces Island, where he died between 17 May and 7 Oct 1656, and is said to have been buried at Point of Graves cemetery in Port
2 CONC smouth.&amp;nbsp; His wife's name was Joanna, who died in 1660.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: large;"&gt;1.&amp;nbsp; THOMAS b. about 1633; m. Temperance __________; d. before 25 Aug. 1697.&lt;br&g
2 CONC t;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; ELIZABETH b. about 1634; unmarried.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; MARY b. about 1637; m. John Partridge 11 Dec. 1660; d. 16 Aug 1722.&amp;nbsp; 8 Chil.&lt;br&gt;2.&amp;nbsp; JOHN b. abo
2 CONC ut 1642; m. Mary Spinney.&lt;br&gt;3.&amp;nbsp; SAMUEL b. about 1644; m. Hannah Spinney.&lt;br&gt;4.&amp;nbsp; WILLIAM b. 5 March 1646, m. Elizabeth Langdon 16 Nov. 1671.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &lt;str
2 CONC ong&gt;Second Generation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;1.&amp;nbsp; Thomas Fernald made a deposition 18 April 1679, giving his age as "46 about."&amp;nbsp; In 1645 Puddington's Islands were leased to him by the agent of Sir Ferdinando Gorges, a
2 CONC nd in 1671, he deeded one of them to his brother William, "for the fulfilling of the last will of our Dere father, Renald Firnild."&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Thomas Fernald married Temperance __________.&amp;nbsp
2 CONC ; He was a shipbuilder.&amp;nbsp; His inventory was returned 25 Aug. 1697.&amp;nbsp; The larger of his two islands, afterwards known as Seavey's Island, was divided by his widow 20 Nov. 1702, among the surviving children.&amp;nbsp; Children:&lt;br&
2 CONC gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; John b. about 1659; unmarried; d. between 1698 and 1702.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Ann b. about 1661; unmarried; living in 1711.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; P
2 CONC atience b. about 1664; m. Ebenezer Evans, (2) Robert Atkins 9 Nov. 1686.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Thomas b. about 1668; m. Elizabeth, dau. of John Hunking: d. before 1699.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; M
2 CONC ary b. about 1671; m. Samuel Pray before 1 Sept. 1697.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; 5. Samuel b. about 1673; m. Susanna Paul, (2) Elizabeth Seward?&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Joanna b. about 1676; m. Char
2 CONC les Kelley 25 May 1698.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Sarah b. about 1678; m. William Henderson 16 July 1700.&amp;nbsp; 2 children.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; 6. Hercules b. about 1680; m. Sarah Hinckes.&l
2 CONC t;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Elizabeth m. Capt. Stephen Eastwick.&amp;nbsp; She d. 26 April 1714, aged 31 years, 2 months and 20 days,&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; as her tomb stone declares.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br
2 CONC &gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: large;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;spa
2 CONC n style="font-size: medium;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span
2 CONC &gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><lin
2 CONC e>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: small;"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;&
2 CONC amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line></content></metadataxml>
