2 TITL William Fernald (1647-1728) Biographic Sketch as written in &quot;Ancestry of Robert Harry McIntire and Helen Annette McIntir...
1 _OID b5934c3b-1a14-4407-8918-bbfc1226fa25
1 DATE 1647-1742
1 PLAC New Hampshire and Maine
1 _DSCR Biographical sketch of William Fernald 91647-1740) and familial information as written in &quot;Ancestry of Robert Harry McIntire And of Helen  Annette McIntire, His Wife,&quot; compiled by Robert Harry McIntire, 1950, Norfolk, VA.
1 _META <metadataxml><content><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: medium;&quot;&gt;The following information about William Fernald is written in the &quot;Ancestry of Robert Harry McIntire and of Helen Annette McIntire, His Wife,: compiled by Ro
2 CONC bert Harry McIntire, 1950, Norfolk, VA. (This source can be found on ancestry.com &lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: medium;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;From pages 198-200 of this source:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/spa
2 CONC n&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: medium;&quot;&gt;792&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; WILLIAM FERNALD, son of Renald and Joanna (Warburton) Fernald, b. Mar. 5, 1647; d. July 5, 1728; m. ELIZABETH LANGDON, dau. of Tobias an
2 CONC d Elizabeth (Sherburne) Langdon, b. Portsmouth, N.H., abt. 1656; d. May 11, 1740.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; He bought &quot;Lay Claim&quot; Island from his brother Thomas in 1671.&amp;nbsp; It remained in the posse
2 CONC ssion of his descendants until about 1790.&amp;nbsp; In 1806, Capt. William Dennett sold the island to Jacob Sheafe, a government agent, for $5,500.&amp;nbsp; It is the present site of the Portsmouth Navy Yard.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbs
2 CONC p;&amp;nbsp; William Fernald, a shipwright, is said to have built a vessel of 148 tons for one Isaac Boyd. He was a selectman by Sir Edwin Andros, Feb. 10, 1686; was referred to as captain in town records of 1695.&amp;nbsp; His last years were spen
2 CONC t on his farm.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Children (FERNALD):&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: medium;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;
2 CONC &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Elizabeth, b. Aug. 17, 1674; d. June 2, 1745; m. Sept. 25, 1701, Clement Deering, son of Lt. Roger and Mary Deering, b. abt. 1680; d. 1742.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span styl
2 CONC e=&quot;font-size: medium;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; William, b. Oct. 31, 1676; d. Dec. 6, 1683.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: m
2 CONC edium;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Tobias, b. Dec. 26, 1678; d. Aug. 18, 1701; m. June 12, 1701, Mary Deering, dau. of Lt. Roger and Mary Deerling.&amp;nbsp; He was a shipwright.&lt;br&g
2 CONC t;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: medium;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Margaret, b. Mar. 27, 1681; d. Jan. 12, 1719; m. May 14, 1702, Solomo
2 CONC n Cotton, a shipwright and innholder, son of John and Sarah (Hearle) Cotton.&amp;nbsp; He d. 1755; m. (2) Judith (Cutts) Pormort, dau. of John and Sarah (Martyn) Cutts, b. July 10, 1683.&amp;nbsp; She was widow of Joseph Pormort, a feltmaker of Ne
2 CONC w Castle who d. 1721.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: medium;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Temperance, b. Sept. 16, 1683; d. May 19
2 CONC , 1761; m. Dec. 12, 1705, John Deering, a sea captain, son of Clement and Joan (Bray) Deering, b. June 17, 1680; d. 1711.&amp;nbsp; She m. (2) abt. 1713, Ebenezer Moore, a shipwright, son of John and Margaret Moore.&amp;nbsp; He d. abt. 1733.&lt;br
2 CONC &gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: medium;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; William, b. May 11, 1686; d. Jan. 12, 1728; m. July 31, 1707, Elizabeth Cotton
2 CONC , dau. of William and Abigail (Pickering) Cotton.&amp;nbsp; She d. abt. 1761.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: medium;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nb
2 CONC sp; Joseph, b. Dec. 21, 1688; d. ante 1724.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: medium;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Sarah, b. Apr. 24, 1691; d. No
2 CONC v. 5, 1748; m. Kittery, Oct. 25, 1711, Jonathan Dam who d. 1749.&amp;nbsp; He was prob. son of John and Sarah (Hall) Dam.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: medium;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&am
2 CONC p;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Lydia, b. Apr. 19, 1693; d. Apr. 17, 1743; m. May 27, 1725, John Clark, a shipwright of Kittery, son of John and Mark Clark.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size
2 CONC : medium;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Benjamin, b. July 11, 1695; d. Apr. 1743; m. abt. 1718, Catherine --------- who survived him.&amp;nbsp; He was a shipwright.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt
2 CONC ;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: medium;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Ebenezer, b. Oct. 7, 1699; d. Jan. 29, 1787; m. Dec. 22, 1724, Patience Mendum, dau. of Jonathan and Sarah (Downing) Mendum, b. abt. 1700; d. Jan
2 CONC . 5, 1775.&amp;nbsp; He was a shipwright.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: medium;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Tobias, b. Dec. 3, 1702; d. May 11, 1761; m. Dec. 22
2 CONC , 1724, Mary Mendum, daug. of Jonathan and Sarah (Downing) Mendum, b. abt. 1703; d. Oct. 16, 1767.&amp;nbsp; He is referred to in town records as captain.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: medium;
2 CONC &quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: medium;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line></content></metadataxml>
