1 _OID cc60e093-d8bf-47c4-81dd-d866a8110ff3
1 DATE 11 Dec 1947
1 PLAC Troy, Waldo, Maine, USA
1 _META <metadataxml><transcription>Found the Complete Obituary for Aunt Ethel Rachel (Meservie) Craig Wingate Carter
2 CONT Mrs. ETHEL R. CARTER
2 CONT TROY, Dec. 11 - Ethel R. Carter, 57, resident here for the past 38 years, died today at the home of her daughter, Mrs. Arthur Moody, after a long illness.
2 CONT She was born Sept. 11, 1890 in Knox, the daughter of Daniel and Adelaide (Mixer) Meservey.
2 CONT Besides her daughter, she is survived by three sisters, Mrs. Medwin Fernald and Mrs. Guy Fernald of Troy, and Mrs. Harry Hammond of Clinton; four brothers, George of Unity, Daniel and Burleigh of Franklin, Mass., and Frank of East Easton, Mass.; fi
2 CONC ve grandchildren; several nieces and nephews.
2 CONT Funeral services will be held at the Troy Corner church, Saturday afternoon at 2 o'clock, Rev. Walter Towle of Unity officiating. Interment will be in Webster Cemetery, Unity. Remains are at the Donald H. Shorey funeral home in Pittsfield, where fr
2 CONC iends may call.</transcription></metadataxml>
