1 _DSCR Bio &amp; Family Info--near verbatim fr Genealogical Dict. for Maine &amp; NH
1 _META <metadataxml><content><line>&lt;font face="book antiqua,palatino"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font size="4" color="#0000ff"&gt;John Pickering&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;font size="3"&gt;(4), &lt;font color="#0000ff"&gt;miller, Portsm., York,&lt;/font&
2 CONC gt; &lt;font color="#0000ff"&gt;m. 17 July 1688, &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ff0000"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#dc143c"&gt;Elizabeth Munden&lt;/font&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt;(2).&amp;nbsp; Portsm. vict. lic. 1692, 1700; tav. 1693, 1
2 CONC 695-98; j. 1695. Called of York 1700 (see 4);&amp;nbsp; gr.j. (Me.) 1701.&amp;nbsp; Lists 330d, 333a, 335b, 337, 57.&amp;nbsp; &lt;font color="#0000ff"&gt;Of Portsm.,&lt;/font&gt; &lt;font color="#0000ff"&gt;weak. he made his will 21 Mar. 1714-5, p
2 CONC rov. 17 Sept.&lt;/font&gt; &lt;font color="#0000ff"&gt;fol.&lt;/font&gt; when he was of York;&amp;nbsp; &lt;font color="#dc143c"&gt;w. &lt;strong&gt;Elizabeth&lt;/strong&gt; and ch. named, w. and fa. executors&lt;/font&gt;; adm. to Thos. Phipps an
2 CONC d Elisha Plaisted &lt;font color="#0000ff"&gt;2 Jan. 1721-2, &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#800080"&gt;at request of s. Thos&lt;/font&gt;.&amp;nbsp; &lt;font color="#dc143c"&gt;The wid. apparently d. by June 1720&lt;/font&gt;.&amp;nbsp; &lt;font col
2 CONC or="#800080"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ch:&amp;nbsp; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mary,&lt;/strong&gt; m. by 1709 to&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#0000ff"&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#008000"&gt;Ambrose &lt;span&gt;Sloper&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/
2 CONC font&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;font color="#339966"&gt;&lt;font color="#800080"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Thomas&lt;/strong&gt;, accus. by&lt;/font&gt; Phebe Tanner (Me. Ct. Apr. 1722&lt;/font&gt;), &lt;font color="#800080"&gt;Millwright, York 1727-9, Portsm
2 CONC . 1730&lt;/font&gt;.&amp;nbsp; &lt;font color="#800080"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Will&lt;/strong&gt;, of Portsm., bound to sea, 18 Mar. 1744-5 (k. [p.552] at Annapolis 1746),&lt;/font&gt; &lt;font color="#ff0000"&gt;&lt;font color="#ff6600"&gt;names w. Dor
2 CONC othy, 8 ch.;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#33cccc"&gt;3 ch. of Thos. and Elizabeth were bp. So. Ch. 1726-1731&lt;/font&gt;.&lt;font color="#800080"&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;strong&gt;Deborah&lt;/strong&gt;, m. 1st aft. 3 May 1719,&lt;/font&gt
2 CONC ;&lt;font color="#ff6600"&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#008000"&gt;&lt;font color="#339966"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#008000"&gt;John Smithson&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;font color="#008000"&gt;(2 ch. bp. So. Ch.);&lt;/font&gt; &lt
2 CONC ;strong&gt;m. 2d&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Joshua Pickering&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/font&gt;(&lt;/font&gt;8). &lt;font color="#3366ff"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;font color="#800080"&gt;Sarah&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;font color="#339966"&gt;&lt;fo
2 CONC nt color="#008000"&gt;m. &lt;strong&gt;Wm. Hooker&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#800080"&gt;(4).&lt;/font&gt;&amp;nbsp; &lt;font color="#0000ff"&gt;&lt;font color="#800080"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Samuel&lt;/strong&
2 CONC gt;, m. aft. Mar. 1724-5&lt;/font&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color="#ff6600"&gt;Sarah (Cotton 1) Walden;&lt;/font&gt; &lt;font color="#800080"&gt;he liv. 1742&lt;/font&gt;, she dead 1744. &lt;font color="#33cccc"&gt;3 ch. liv. 1754&lt;/font&gt;. &lt
2 CONC ;font color="#800080"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Daniel&lt;/strong&gt;, bp. No. Ch. 5 Aug. 1711, liv. 1721.&lt;/font&gt; Adm. on est. of one &lt;font color="#800080"&gt;Daniel of Portsm. gr. 1765 to&lt;/font&gt; &lt;font color="#ff6600"&gt;wid. Dorothy&lt;/f
2 CONC ont&gt;.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt; </line></content></metadataxml>
