1 PLAC Maine &amp; New Hampshire
1 _DSCR Capt William Fernald, his wife, Elizabeth Langdon, and their children as written in Genealogical Dictionary of Maine &amp; New Hampshire by Sybil Noyes, Charles Thornton Libby &amp; Goodwin Davis; originally Published in Portland, Maine 1928 - 1939
2 CONC . Genealogical 
1 _META <metadataxml><content><line>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;The following is written in &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt; Genealogical Dictionary of Maine &amp;amp; New Hampshire&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt; by Sybil Noyes, Charles Thornton Lib
2 CONC by &amp;amp; Goodwin Davis; originally Published in Portland, Maine 1928 - 1939. Genealogical Publishing Company.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medium;"&gt;Page 231:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: medi
2 CONC um;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;FERNALD&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; CAPT WILLIAM&lt;/strong&gt;(2), b. 5 Mar. 1646-7, shipwright.&amp;nbsp; Lieut. and Dep. 1684.&amp;nbsp; Gr.j. 1682, 1693; jury, foreman, 1695, 1701. Selectm. 1674, 1692
2 CONC -1697.&amp;nbsp; Lists 36, 32, 98, 239b, 291, 293, 296-298.&amp;nbsp; D. 5 July 1728. Wife Elizabeth Langdon, m. 16 Nov. 1671, d. 11 May 1740. Ch:&amp;nbsp; &lt;strong&gt;Elizabeth, &lt;/strong&gt;b. 17 Aug. 1674, mar. Clement Deering(8).&amp;nbsp
2 CONC ; &lt;strong&gt;William, &lt;/strong&gt;b. 31 Oct. 1676, d. 6 Dec. 1683.&amp;nbsp; &lt;strong&gt;Tobias, &lt;/strong&gt;b. 26 Dec. 1678, shipwright, m. 12 June 1701 Mary Deering(8), d. 6 Dec. 1701. 1 dau. b. 19 Mar. 1701-2. He bot 22 Aug. 1700 th
2 CONC e Richard Cutt homestead, which his wid. 6 Apr. 1704 sold to his father, who made it his homestead.&amp;nbsp; &lt;strong&gt;Margaret, &lt;/strong&gt;b. 27 Mar. 1681, mar. Solomon Cotton(2).&amp;nbsp; &lt;strong&gt;Temperance, &lt;/strong&gt;b. 16 S
2 CONC ep. 1683, mar. John Deering(1). &amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;William, &lt;/strong&gt;b. 11 May 1686, m. 31 July 1707 Elizabeth Cotton(7).&amp;nbsp; He d. 12 Jan. 1728; her will 1756-1761. 7 ch. &lt;strong&gt;Joseph, &lt;/strong&gt;b. 21 Dec. 1688, d. ea
2 CONC rly.&amp;nbsp; &lt;strong&gt;Sarah, &lt;/strong&gt;b. 24 Apr. 1691, m Jonathan Dam(3). &amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Lydia, &lt;/strong&gt;b. 19 Apr. 1693, m. John Clark(20 jr.). &amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Benjamin, &lt;/strong&gt;b. 11 July 1695, shipwrigh
2 CONC t, d. before 1743. List 291.&amp;nbsp; Wife Catherine surv. 4 liv. ch. 1742.&amp;nbsp; &lt;strong&gt;Nathaniel, &lt;/strong&gt;b. 12 June 1697, tailor, d. 18 Sep. 1771, m. 7 Apr. 1720 Margaret Tripe.&amp;nbsp; 7 ch. &lt;strong&gt;Ebenezer, &lt;/str
2 CONC ong&gt;b. 7 Oct. 1699, shipwright, m. 22 Dec. 1724 Patience Mendum, who d. 5 Jan. 1775.&amp;nbsp; He d. 29 Jan. 1787. 12 ch.&amp;nbsp; &lt;strong&gt;Tobias, &lt;/strong&gt;Capt., b. 3 Dec. 1702, m. 22 Dec. 1724 Mary Mendum, who d. 10 Oct. 1767. H
2 CONC e d. 11 May 1761. 7 ch.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</line></content></metadataxml>
