2 TITL ErleMonument2
1 _OID fbc46cb6-3b4a-4253-99da-c163a74a1ec3
1 DATE 2008
1 PLAC St. Mary's Church East Morden, England
1 _DSCR Inside the St. Mary's church in east Morden are the remains of a monument to Thomas Earle and three of his children that predeceased him. It has been split in two with half each side of the entrance to the bell tower. This picture was taken in 2008
2 CONC . It showsthe figure of Thomas Erle in complete armour, on bended knee, in the act of homage. 
2 CONT The original inscription read:-
2 CONT 
2 CONT Here liethe buryed the bodye of Thomas Earle, the
2 CONT sone of Walter Earle, whoe departed from this lyff the 16 daye of Marche in the yeare of our Lorde God 1597. 
2 CONT his sons wer 4, his daughters 2, of who me John 
2 CONT Thomas and Doritjie are desecid, and remayneth now livynge Walter, Christopher, and Elizabeth. 
2 CONT 
1 _META <metadataxml><cemetery /><transcription /></metadataxml>
